# Testing

## Commands

```bash
npm run test          # unit tests
npm run test:watch    # watch mode
npm run test:cov      # coverage
npm run test:integration  # integration (supertest)
```

Run a single file:
- Unit: `npx jest <pattern>`
- Integration: `npx jest --config ./test/jest-integration.json <file>`

## Unit Tests (`*.spec.ts`)

- Colocate with source: `bands.service.spec.ts` next to `bands.service.ts`.
- Use `Test.createTestingModule()` for NestJS DI setup.
- Mock repositories with `{ provide: getRepositoryToken(Entity), useValue: mockRepo }`.
- Test one public method per `describe` block; use `it` not `test`.

```typescript
describe('BandsService', () => {
  describe('findAll', () => {
    it('returns paginated bands', async () => { ... });
  });
});
```

## Integration Tests (`*.integration-spec.ts`)

- Live in `test/`; use supertest against a real NestJS app instance.
- Config: `test/jest-integration.json`.

## Coverage

- Focus coverage on services (business logic), not controllers or modules.
- `no-explicit-any` is OFF — acceptable in test mocks.
